source: Chase, K.A., Brigham, C.E., et al. (2014) Fitness Norms for the Plank Exercise. International Journal of Exercise Science and Applied Kinesiology, 8(2)
source_notes: Norms originally established for collegiate athletes ages 18–25. Values are applied uniformly across adult age groups as a general standard. Reference: Males M=117.66±53.49s, Females M=106.15±49.52s
protocol: Maintain a straight line from head to heels on forearms and toes. Terminate when form breaks.
